> OK. I've dropped a preliminary version in 
> /pub/crypt/ripem/incoming/rsaref-2.0+.tar.gz 
> 
> I've only tested this version on Sun OS 4.1.x and Linux.
> 
> I've been very conservative. Not much weird code in here. A lot less
> than before. Much of the weirdness is concentrated in a file longlong.h
> which should make it relatively easy to add assembler for the critical
> operation of nxn->2n bit multiply for whatever platforms inspire people.
> 
> Best to use gcc 2.x on most platforms because it will take advantage
> of the "unsigned long long" stuff.
> 
> Lightly tested would best describe it. I've grabbed code from my 
> experimental stuff and the RSAREF from RIPEM 1.1, cobbled it all 
> together and it seems to work. 
> 
> Let me know how it goes.
> 
> Mark
