To: ripem-dev@ripem.msu.edu
Subject: Comments on 1.3a1 release


Hi Mark. I looked at RIPEM 1.3a1 you put together.  Thanks for
turning it around so quickly.  I have a few logistical comments:

* ripem-encrypt-elm, ripem-encrypt-old clash with ripem-encrypt when
unzipping on MS-DOS.  I know these are only relevant for UNIX, but
maybe something can be done.

The following also reflect changes I made in the release and are
detailed in the changes.txt file:

* Need to remove ripem/main/adduser.* since AddUniqueUserToList was
moved to ripem/cmdline/ripemcmd.c.  

* Need to remove redundant ripem/main/global.h since all makefiles
include /rsaref/source anyway.

* Need to remove ripem/main/list.h and listprot.h. These declarations
are now in ripem.h and no source includes these files.

* Need to remove ripem/main/ripemglo.h since there are no more globals.

* Need to remove ripem/main/ripempro.h since these functions are now
static and declared inside ripemmai.c.  No source files include
ripempro.h.

* Need to removed len_UTC and put_UTC from ripem/main/keyderpr.h
since they are static functions and declared inside keyder.c.

Also, ripem/cmdline/usagemsg.c still says 1.2b, not 1.3a1.  And
ripem/main/version.h says 1.2a, which makes this a good time to ask
what version.h is for?  I haven't ever seen any source files include
it.

That's all for now.

- Jeff


